calls.name: AddInventoryItems
calls.summary: Add inventory items. Up to 10,000 stacks of items can be added to a single inventory collection. Stack size is uncapped.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type, entity identifier and container details, will add the specified inventory items.

calls.name: AddVirtualCurrencies
calls.summary: Increase virtual currencies amount.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type, entity identifier and container details, will increase the entity's currencies by a specific amount.

calls.name: ConsumeInventoryItems
calls.summary: Consume inventory items.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type, entity identifier and container details, will consume the specified inventory items.

calls.name: CreateDraftItem
calls.summary: Creates a new item in the working catalog using provided metadata.
calls.requestDetails: The item will not be published to the public catalog until the PublishItem API is called for the item.

calls.name: CreateUploadUrls
calls.summary: Creates one or more upload URLs which can be used by the client to upload raw file data. Content URls and uploaded content will be garbage collected after 24 hours if not attached to a draft or published item. Detailed pricing info around uploading content can be found here: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/gaming/playfab/features/pricing/meters/catalog-meters
calls.requestDetails: Upload URLs point to Azure Blobs; clients must follow the Microsoft Azure Storage Blob Service REST API pattern for uploading content. The response contains upload URLs and IDs for each file. The IDs and URLs returned must be added to the item metadata and committed using the CreateDraftItem or UpdateDraftItem Item APIs.

calls.name: CreateView
calls.summary: Creates a new view in the catalog using provided metadata.

calls.name: DeleteEntityItemReviews
calls.summary: Deletes all reviews, helpfulness votes, and ratings submitted by the entity specified.

calls.name: DeleteInventoryCollection
calls.summary: Delete an Inventory Collection. More information about Inventory Collections can be found here: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/gaming/playfab/features/economy-v2/inventory/collections
calls.requestDetails: Delete an Inventory Collection by the specified Id for an Entity

calls.name: DeleteInventoryItems
calls.summary: Delete inventory items
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type, entity identifier and container details, will delete the entity's inventory items

calls.name: DeleteItem
calls.summary: Removes an item from working catalog and all published versions from the public catalog.

calls.name: DeleteView
calls.summary: Deletes a catalog view and the associated blob.

calls.name: EvaluateDropTable
calls.summary: Evaluate a drop table and returns a randomly selected pool. The random selection is based on the weights of the pools in the drop table.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity token and id, evaluate a drop table and return the evaluated pool.

calls.name: ExecuteInventoryOperations
calls.summary: Execute a list of Inventory Operations. A maximum list of 50 operations can be performed by a single request. There is also a limit to 300 items that can be modified/added in a single request. For example, adding a bundle with 50 items counts as 50 items modified. All operations must be done within a single inventory collection. This API has a reduced RPS compared to an individual inventory operation with Player Entities limited to 60 requests in 90 seconds.
calls.requestDetails: Execute a list of Inventory Operations for an Entity

calls.name: ExecuteTransferOperations
calls.summary: Transfer a list of inventory items. A maximum list of 50 operations can be performed by a single request. When the response code is 202, one or more operations did not complete within the timeframe of the request. You can identify the pending operations by looking for OperationStatus = 'InProgress'. You can check on the operation status at anytime within 1 day of the request by passing the TransactionToken to the GetInventoryOperationStatus API.
calls.requestDetails: Transfer the specified list of inventory items of an entity's container Id to another entity's container Id.

calls.name: GetAccessTokens
calls.summary: Get Access Tokens
calls.requestDetails: Get a set of Access Tokens to interact with the specified marketplace

calls.name: GetCatalogConfig
calls.summary: Gets the configuration for the catalog. Only Title Entities can call this API. There is a limit of 100 requests in 10 seconds for this API. More information about the Catalog Config can be found here: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/gaming/playfab/features/economy-v2/settings

calls.name: GetDraftItem
calls.summary: Retrieves an item from the working catalog. This item represents the current working state of the item. GetDraftItem does not work off a cache of the Catalog and should be used when trying to get recent item updates. However, please note that item references data is cached and may take a few moments for changes to propagate.

calls.name: GetDraftItems
calls.summary: Retrieves a paginated list of the items from the draft catalog. Up to 50 IDs can be retrieved in a single request. GetDraftItems does not work off a cache of the Catalog and should be used when trying to get recent item updates.

calls.name: GetEntityDraftItems
calls.summary: Retrieves a paginated list of the items from the draft catalog created by the Entity. Up to 50 items can be returned at once. You can use continuation tokens to paginate through results that return greater than the limit. GetEntityDraftItems does not work off a cache of the Catalog and should be used when trying to get recent item updates.

calls.name: GetEntityItemReview
calls.summary: Gets the submitted review for the specified item by the authenticated entity. Individual ratings and reviews data update in near real time with delays within a few seconds.

calls.name: GetInventoryCollectionIds
calls.summary: Get Inventory Collection Ids. Up to 50 Ids can be returned at once (or 250 with response compression enabled). You can use continuation tokens to paginate through results that return greater than the limit. It can take a few seconds for new collection Ids to show up.
calls.requestDetails: Get a list of Inventory Collection Ids for the specified Entity

calls.name: GetInventoryItems
calls.summary: Get current inventory items.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity type, entity identifier and container details, will get the entity's inventory items.

calls.name: GetInventoryOperationStatus
calls.summary: Get the status of an inventory operation using an OperationToken. You can check on the operation status at anytime within 1 day of the request by passing the TransactionToken to the this API.
calls.requestDetails: Get the status of an Inventory Operation using an OperationToken.

calls.name: GetItem
calls.summary: Retrieves an item from the public catalog. GetItem does not work off a cache of the Catalog and should be used when trying to get recent item updates. However, please note that item references data is cached and may take a few moments for changes to propagate.

calls.name: GetItemContainers
calls.summary: Search for a given item and return a set of bundles and stores containing the item. Up to 50 items can be returned at once. You can use continuation tokens to paginate through results that return greater than the limit. This API is intended for tooling/automation scenarios and has a reduced RPS with Player Entities limited to 30 requests in 300 seconds and Title Entities limited to 100 requests in 10 seconds.
calls.requestDetails: Given an item, return a set of bundles and stores containing the item.
